<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n10092i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10092i">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10092i"> 92(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> history is mute</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Depuis la chute de la dynastie carlovingienne jusqu&apos;aux premiers Cap&eacute;tiens, <mark>l&apos;histoire est muette</mark> sur les Postes, et ce silence en dit plus que de longs r&eacute;cits sur le peu de s&eacute;curit&eacute; que pr&eacute;sentaient en France les voies de communication, au moment o&ugrave; s&apos;&eacute;tablit le r&eacute;gime f&eacute;odal. <font color="green">[From the fall of the Carolingian Dynasty until the first Capets, history is mute on the subject of the Post and this silence says more than the longest accounts about the lack of safety on the French transportation routes at the time of the establishment of feudalism.]</font> <small> Arthur de Rothschild, <a name="ARHD" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ARHD"><cite title="source">Histoire de la poste</cite></a> (1876) 102</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
